    "contenu": "Below is the structured content from the document, organized by each type of liqueur and their main descriptors:\n\n### Liqueurs and Descriptions \n\n1. **Cointreau**\n   - **Type:** Triple sec (orange liqueur)\n   - **Description:** Characterized by balance of sweetness, body, and clean orange flavors; noted for adding brightness to drinks; significantly impacts cocktails like the Margarita and Sidecar, enhancing their taste distinctly.\n\n2. **Galliano L’Autentico**\n   - **Type:** Herbal liqueur\n   - **Description:** Reestablished to its historic recipe featuring less sweetness and lower alcohol content (42.3% ABV), enhancing the vanilla and anise flavors along with other botanicals.\n\n3. **Grand Marnier**\n   - **Type:** Blend of cognac and triple sec\n   - **Description:** Sweeter than Cointreau; has a robust, richer profile enhancing the flavor quality.\n\n4. **Kalani Ron de Coco Coconut Liqueur**\n   - **Type:** Coconut liqueur\n   - **Description:** Touted as the most natural-tasting coconut liqueur; sourced from Mexico's Yucatán Peninsula, incorporates locally grown coconuts and sugarcane.\n\n5. **Luxardo Maraschino Liqueur**\n   - **Type:** Cherry-flavored liqueur\n   - **Description:** Known for its distinct funkiness from using whole marasca cherries in distillation; adds complexity to drinks like the Aviation.\n\n6. **Marie Brizard White Crème de Cacao**\n   - **Type:** Chocolate liqueur\n   - **Description:** Distilled from cocoa beans, flavored with vanilla; known for its creamy texture and pure, natural flavors; distinctly different from other chocolate liqueurs.\n\n7. **Rothman & Winter Orchard Apricot Liqueur**\n   - **Type:** Fruit liqueur\n   - **Description:** Made from apricot juice and eau-de-vie distilled from apricots; introduces subtle, fresh apricot flavors into drinks with a balance that allows incorporation of other sweet ingredients.\n\n8. **Strega**\n   - **Type:** Herbal liqueur\n   - **Description:** Compares in color and complexity to yellow Chartreuse; distinguishes itself with a stronger presence of anise and vanilla flavors, recommended in very tiny amounts to maintain balance in drinks."
