    "contenu": "The document provides recipes for three different cocktails, each with a name, creator, recipe, and preparation instructions. Here's a structured breakdown of each cocktail:\n\n### 1. Cirque Swizzle\n- **Creator:** Jessica Gonzalez, 2011\n- **Description:** This drink’s pretty pink color gives it a cotton candy–like appearance.\n- **Ingredients:**\n  - 1½ ounces Anchor Junipero Gin\n  - ½ ounce Yellow Chartreuse\n  - 1 teaspoon Crème Yvette, plus more for topping the drink\n  - ¼ ounce Lemon Juice\n  - ¼ ounce Vanilla Syrup\n  - ¼ ounce Simple Syrup\n- **Instructions:** \n  - Dry shake all the ingredients, then dump into a pilsner glass filled with crushed ice. \n  - Swizzle until cold, then top with a thin layer of Crème Yvette. Serve with a straw. \n  - No garnish.\n\n### 2. Coffey Park Swizzle\n- **Creator:** Alex Day, 2008\n- **Description:** This was the first of many sherry cocktails created. It's a tribute to the Queen’s Park Swizzle, the most classic drink in the category.\n- **Ingredients:**\n  - 1 ounce Barbancourt 3-star Rum\n  - 1 ounce Lustau Amontillado Sherry\n  - ¼ ounce Velvet Falernum\n  - ¼ ounce Lime Juice\n  - ¾ ounce Ginger Syrup\n  - 3 dashes Angostura Bitters\n  - Garnish: 1 Mint Sprig\n- **Instructions:** \n  - Whip all the ingredients (except the bitters), shaking with a few pieces of crushed ice just until incorporated. \n  - Strain into a pilsner glass filled with crushed ice. \n  - Swizzle until cold. Add the bitters and swizzle them into the top of the drink. \n  - Garnish with the mint sprig and serve with a straw.\n\n### 3. DJ Flamethrower\n- **Creator:** Joaquín Simó, 2012\n- **Description:** Some of our favorite ingredient pairings are represented in this drink: grapefruit and cinnamon, tequila and chiles, and tequila and mezcal."
