    "source": "a_with_and_step_of",
    "contenu": "### Fried Onion Rings Instructions\n\n- **Step 1:** Dip onion rings first in beaten eggs, allowing excess to drip off.\n- **Step 2:** Coat evenly with flour, tap off excess.\n- **Step 3:** Carefully slip into hot oil, fry until golden brown (~3 minutes).\n- **Step 4:** Using tongs or a wire skimmer, transfer to paper towels to drain.\n- **Step 5:** Sprinkle with salt.\n\n### Crab Salad with Onion Rings Preparation\n\n- **Step 1:** Serve by scooping a bite-sized mound of crab salad onto a spoon.\n- **Step 2:** Top with a fried onion ring.\n- **Step 3:** Arrange on a tray and serve.\n\n### Additional Tips\n\n- **Coconut Cream:** If unsweetened coconut cream is unavailable, open a can of unsweetened coconut milk and scoop off the thick layer of cream.\n- **Ras el hanout:** Consists of a mix of spices including mace, cinnamon, coriander, cumin, turmeric, and black peppercorns. Popular in North African and Middle Eastern kitchens. Available in specialized shops.\n- **Alternative Serving Suggestion:** For a different serving, omit onion rings and serve the crab salad atop toasted baguette slices.\n\n### Wine Pairing: Prosecco\n\n- **Info:** Prosecco is a versatile sparkling wine, suitable for serving with hors d'oeuvres at home or in a restaurant. It pairs well with appetizers without requiring toothpicks or additional napkins. \n- **Preparation & Serving:** Can be made ahead and served à la minute. Refrigerates well.\n  \n### Personal Recommendation\n- **Evan:** Recommends visiting Vij's restaurant in Canada for its unique blend of Indian culinary tradition with Western cuisine integrated with Pacific Northwest ingredients. Prefers Prosecco to Kingfisher or Taj Mahal beers due predominantly to the exquisite pairing of Prosecco with dishes like Crab and Prosecco which exemplify the sweet crab meat and coconut milk harmonizing with Prosecco's slight heat and sweetness. Suggests a dry Prosecco and being generous with quantity if using canned crab. Recommends